Sentencas: An efficient controller is greatly important for the quick load-following response of solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) power systems, which is vital for the fuel utilization and the life of the stack.
Titulo: Dynamic modeling of electrical characteristics of solid oxide fuel cells using fractional derivatives

Sentencas: To design such a controller, an accurate dynamic model of SOFC electrical characteristics is critical.
Titulo: Dynamic modeling of electrical characteristics of solid oxide fuel cells using fractional derivatives

Sentencas: Here an integer order dynamic model is established by a transient equivalent circuit, and then a fractional order dynamic model is done in the perspective of the fractional derivatives theory.
Titulo: Dynamic modeling of electrical characteristics of solid oxide fuel cells using fractional derivatives

Sentencas: The parameters of the dynamic models then are optimized via genetic algorithms according to electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS) experimental data.
Titulo: Dynamic modeling of electrical characteristics of solid oxide fuel cells using fractional derivatives

Sentencas: Finally, the dynamic response experiments from the models are studied.
Titulo: Dynamic modeling of electrical characteristics of solid oxide fuel cells using fractional derivatives

Sentencas: The results show that the fractional order dynamic model has higher accuracy for representing the dynamics of the SOFC electrical characteristics, which lays a solid foundation for the controller based on the accurate model.
Titulo: Dynamic modeling of electrical characteristics of solid oxide fuel cells using fractional derivatives
